label: AB_oF8_22_a_c-001
title: Low temperature FeS Structure
comments:
This is the stable structure of iron sulfide below 242K.  Above that temperature it is in the \href{current_web_home_dir/AB_cF8_216_a_c-001}{zincblende ($B3$) structure}. (Wintenberger, 1978). 
 This data was taken at 81K.  We follow (Villars, 2016) and rearrange the axis, as well as reversing the positions of the iron and sulfur atoms.
